FBIS4-3950 "drchi080_v_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-080 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 TAIWAN KMT Official Named New CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY Chief KMT Official Named New CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY Chief OW2604085094 Taipei CNA in English 0752 GMT 26 Apr 94 OW2604085094 Taipei CNA English BFN [By Sofia Wu] [Text] Taipei, April 26 (CNA) -- Shih Ke-min, deputy director of the Cultural Affairs Department of the ruling Kuomintang [KMT], has been named the next president of the CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY [CNA]. Shih, 58, will succeed P.P. Tang, who will become president of the KMT-run CENTRAL DAILY NEWS. An experienced journalist, Shih joined the Tainan-based CHINA DAILY NEWS shortly after he graduated from National Taiwan Normal University. He later became a UNITED DAILY NEWS correspondent and bureau chief in Washington, D.C. He returned to Taipei last May to assume the KMT post after living in the U.S. for 25 years. He will assume his new post after a ceremony to be held sometime next month.
